  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite being published in 2021 by Leuven University Press, \"Protagonists of War\" has yet to garner external citations or significant public mentions, indicating a limited visibility in both academic and community conversations.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Upon its release, \"Protagonists of War\" sought to explore complex themes surrounding conflict and human agency. However, as of the latest data, it has not generated measurable academic discourse, with no citations recorded in platforms such as OpenAlex. This absence of citations may suggest a niche appeal or a delayed reception within scholarly circles.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The work has not sparked discussions on high-fidelity social and community platforms, such as Reddit, Wikipedia, or Bluesky, which might contribute to its limited visibility in public domains. The lack of presence on such platforms indicates that, while the subject matter may be relevant, it has not yet resonated enough to provoke community discourse or engagement.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">From a commercial perspective, the book demonstrates a strong linkage to sales channels, reflected by its availability on commercial sites like Amazon and Goodreads. This accessibility could potentially enhance its reach within targeted audiences, despite the current lack of scholarly attention.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, \"Protagonists of War\" has potential for further exploration and dissemination, but as of now, the data suggests a need for greater promotion and engagement strategies to establish a foothold within both academic and public conversations regarding its themes and insights.</p>",
